patch:
commit 798f008a309d82fb190348bb39db1888da746949
Author: John Hubbard <jhubbard@nvidia.com>
Date:   Mon Jul 20 13:22:26 2020 -0700

    memory-to-memory-format: remove redundant PIO structs

    Remove the PIO (Programmed I/O) structs from all existing
    memory-to-memory-format class header files, because they are unnecessary
    and add to the maintenance burden. The offsets suffice for programming
    these classes.

    This is not applied to every class in this directory: cl0039.h is left
    alone. That's because it contains some small in-line comments in the
    struct, which are helpful, and yet small. It's not a maintenance burden
    because it's the first version of the class, and is small.

    Reviewed-by: Maneet Singh
    Signed-off-by: John Hubbard <jhubbard@nvidia.com>
---
 classes/memory-to-memory-format/cl5039.h |  42 -----------
 classes/memory-to-memory-format/cl9039.h | 115 -------------------------------
 2 files changed, 157 deletions(-)

