Author: John Hubbard <jhubbard@nvidia.com>
Date:   Mon Jul 20 11:48:12 2020 -0700

    Ampere: compute class header files

    This adds four new Ampere files, plus one older file that had been
    missed long ago. It also removes the PIO (Programmed I/O) structs from
    all existing compute class header files. The struct removal is done
    because they are unnecessary and add to the maintenance burden. The
    offsets suffice for programming these classes.

    Reviewed-by: Andy Ritger <aritger@nvidia.com>
    Signed-off-by: John Hubbard <jhubbard@nvidia.com>
